data.title: Poster of Hermann Schubert
data.meta_description: Hermann Schubert was a German mathematiciaan who worked on parts of algebraic geometry that involve a finite number of solutions. This is called Enumerative Geometry.
data.text:
Hermann Schubert was a German mathematiciaan who worked on parts of algebraic geometry that involve a finite number of solutions. This is called Enumerative Geometry.

Find out more at: https://mathshistory.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Schubert/
